author: Max
description:
Phylicia Rashad, Denée Benton, Jordan Donica, and more reflect on the Black Elite community in New York during the Gilded Age. They discuss Peggy (Benton)'s aspirations as a young black woman, racism's impact on access to medical care, and the importance of representation during this era.
